org.stekikun.dolmen.automaton

Class DFA.State

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.stekikun.dolmen.automaton.DFA.State
  • Enclosing class:
    DFA

    public static final class DFA.State
extends Object
    A state in the (tagged) deterministic finite automaton corresponds to a set of states in the non-deterministic automaton, each being associated with a memory map.

    NFA States of the form NFA.Event.onChars(int) are accounted for in others, and are indexed by the corresponding character set index. Besides, there can be at most one state of the form NFA.Event.toAction(int), i.e. a final state, in which case the DFA state is final itself. If there were more than one final state, there would be ambiguity as to what action should be performed when accepting the input.
